@NODE INSTA "Installing Gunbee F-99"

@{b}REQUIREMENTS@{ub}

- Amiga AGA computer
- A hard disk
- 1 Mb of Chip-Ram free
- 1 Mb of Fast-Ram free

A joystick with 2nd. fire button is highly reccomended.


@{b}CD/FLOPPY DISK NOTE (only Demo Version)@{ub}

Gunbee F-99 needs following files (already available in your Workbench):

- LIBS/mathtrans.library
- LIBS/diskfont.library
- FONT/topaz
- FONT/topaz.font

This GUNBEE F-99 DEMO may also be played also from floppy disk. Just make it
bootable, copy the required files and create a 'startup-sequence' file to
automatically execute the game.


@{b}IMPORTANT@{ub}

Gunbee F-99 may crash if you have installed a "mathtrans.library" other than
the original one supplied with the Workbench 3.x diskettes.

@ENDNODE
 

@NODE SHORT "Introduction"

@{b}THE STORY...@{ub}

For many years, Valstyx was a peaceful planet in the Universe. Five Magic
Crystals owned by Lady Akiko, the princess of Valstyx, guaranteed the power
and stability to the whole planet.

But one day things changed. Strange beasts and bizarre machines suddenly
invaded the planet. It was being taken over by Lord Khenmir's evil forces.

In a surpresive attack, the Royal Soldiers were unable to defend Akiko's
Palace. And while the chaos involved the kingdom, the 5 Magic Crystals
were stolen by Lord Khenmir, and the princess was kidnapped.

Designed with the very best of Valstyx technology, you, as Kiara McGuire,
will pilot the GUNBEE F-99, a mobile suit developed by the Royal Engineers
with the hope to recover the 5 Magic Crystals, to defeat Lord Khenmir's
big guardians, and succeed in the save of the princess Akiko.


Good luck!

@ENDNODE


@NODE PLAYN "Playing Gunbee F-99"

@{b}01.- THE CONTROLS@{ub}

You control Gunbee F-99 with the joystick in port 1:

Move toward any direction to fly.
Press Fire 1 quickly to shoot.
Press Fire 1 longer to shoot a Firebeam.
Press Fire 2 to throw a bomb.

The 'space key' can be used as 2nd. firebutton.

Alternatively you can use the Keyboard:

Cursors Keys to fly.
Left AMIGA quickly to shoot.
Left AMIGA longer to launch a Firebeam.
Left ALT to throw a bomb.

In-Game Keys:

Press "P" to pause the game, again to resume.
Press "ESC" to exit current game and return to menu.


@{b}02.- GUNBEE F-99 WEAPONS@{ub}

THE STANDARD WEAPONS (upgradeable by collecting more Power-Up Bells)

THE FIREBEAM...

THE BOMB...

MACHINEGUN... (available for Gunbee F-99P Planetary Type)


@{b}03.- THE BELLS@{ub}

Bells are one of the most important items in the game. These are hidden in
some Smiling Clouds. Shoot the clouds to release a bell. First time will be
a gold bell, but if you continue shooting it will change colour.

To collect bells simply fly over these and you will get one of the
following  results:

Gold Bell  - Points   : 500 points.
Blue Bell  - Speed Up : improves Gunbee flying speed.
Green Bell - Power Up : improves Gunbee fire power, then activate next weapon.
White Bell - Shield   : activate Gunbee Shield 20 seconds (limited quantity).
Red Bell   - Beam Up  : supply an extra Firebeam.
Black Bell - Damage   : these must be avoided as Gunbee will lose its arms
                        (and ability to throw bombs).


@{b}04.- THE FLYING AMBULANCE@{ub}


@{b}05.- THE FLYING BASKET@{ub}

The colorful winged Flying Basket does the job of a 'bell collector'. It is
released when an entire enemy wave is shootdown, while some Smiling Clouds
are still flying in the sky.

Another use of the Bells is to land them into the Flying Basket, by knocking
the Bells around the screen with accurate and well timed shoots.

Each time 10 Bells are knocked into the Flying Basket, the player will be
rewarded with an Extra-Live. Black Bells are also valid.

Bells are not the only objects you may put into the Flying Basket.


@{b}06.- THE KITTY-KATRANSPORT CLOUD@{ub}


@{b}07.- KITTY-KATRANSPORT ITEMS@{ub}

THE MACHINEGUN AMMO CLIPS

THE HIGH FIREBEAM

THE MAGIC CRYSTALS
                               
To recover a Magic Crystal, it must be put into the Flying Basket, by knocking
it around the screen with accurate shoots. Read carefully the 'Flying Basket'
explanation to understand how a Basket are released.

THE GB01/P KIT (GUNBEE F-99P PLANETARY TYPE)

Upgrades the Gunbee F-99 into a F-99P Planetary Type, providing stabilizers
to eliminate the turbulence found in very high atmospheres (like the one in
the fourth level). A two hand-held MachineGun weapon is also provided.


@{b}08.- GROUND ATTACK@{ub}
                                                             

@{b}09.- THE PLAYER WINDOW STATUS@{Ub}


@{b}10.- THE HIGH SCORE TABLE@{Ub}

Important Note: High-Scores are saved only when you QUIT the game.


@ENDNODE


@NODE OPTIO "Options Screen"

@{b}THE OPTIONS SCREEN@{ub}


@{b}01.- GAME MODES@{ub}

Press fire button to switch between Honey or Story mode.

@{b}Story Mode@{ub}

All the rules explained in this manual applies to this mode.

The main objective of this mode is to succefully save lovely Lady Akiko
by collecting all 5 Magic Crystals.

The word 'ABILITY' is the only key to 'SURVIVE' in Story Mode because the
player must use all his ability to pay attention to hardest rules, like:

- collect 10 Bells into the Flying Baskets to get further extralives
- collect Kitty-Katransport Clouds Items (specially the Magic Crystals)
- possibility to miss High Firebeam or GB01/P Kit
- avoid more shoots or attack modes from enemies or big guardians

@{b}Honey Mode@{ub}

Almost all the rules explained in this manual applies to this mode,
with the following exceptions:

- Player begins with 5 lives
- Kitty-Katransport Cloud not available
- Magic Crystals are not available
- KTCS Items not available (GB01/P kit, MG AmmoClip and High Firebeam)
- Gunbee F99P Planetary Mode not available in Level 4
- Turbulence not available in Level 4
- Flying Ambulance always available
- High Firebeam always available
- Player begins with 5 Firebeams
- ExtraLives every 100,000 points
- No ExtraLives if 10 Bells are collected into Flying Basket
- Enemy Bases's shoot (ground attack) kills the player
- Less enemy attack initiative (shoots)
- Big Guardians shoots a bit slow, or less attack modes.

The objective of this mode is to allow the player to learn the rules of the
game, to plan a bit of strategy and to practice useful tactics for critical
situations somewhere in the levels.

Surviving is more easy as the player is provided with more initial lives and
a faster way to get extra lives. Also the no need to constantly pay attention
to Katransport Items (like Crystals) and other rules (for ex. knocking bells
into the Baskets to get further extralives) allow the player to safely fly
over the screen without worrying about all that.

@{b}2.- MUSIC@{ub}

