@{b}4.- LEVEL SELECTION@{ub}

@ENDNODE





@NODE TIPS "Tips & Tricks"

@{b}GUNBEE F99 TIPS@{ub}

- When beginning a level, collect as soon as possible useful bells.
  Green and Blue bells will improve drastically your flight performance.

- The more powerful is your Gunbee F99, less performance is lost if you die.

- Beware when flying under the Clouds. Slow enemy shots may be flying below.

- If you die, put your effort to search inmediatelly a Green bell. You may
  quickly recover your previous fast firing rate.

- If your shooting rate is slow, then don't shoot quickly. Use paused and
  accurate shoots instead, until you power-up a bit more (Green Bells).

- Don't wast White Bells. Shields are limited to 1 or 2 for each level.

- Ground enemy bases destroyed may reward an Extra Live Bonus.

@ENDNODE


