@{b}Some words from the author...@{ub}

GUNBEE F-99 is the first completed videogame on any platform created in Perú
and spreaded outside the country. Other local productions, back in early '90
on the Commodore 64 scene, were also created by Twin Eagles (TEG).

I formed TEG with the hope to make videogames as a retribution for our
favourite computer. Unfortunately for us, in those days it was very hard to
get in contact with outside people, and after a large activity in our scene
the members left the group and everything stopped. In early 1997 I got an
internet account and I felt the need to code something again, and so
Gunbee F-99 was born. Actually I'm the only member of Twin Eagles.
  
@ENDNODE



